      <div class="module">        
	<h3>Related Documents</h3>      
	<ul>
	
	<li><a href="/en/money_and_tax/tax/capital_taxes/capital_gains_tax.html">Capital Gains Tax</a><br>Capital Gains Tax is charged on the capital gain or profit made on the disposal of an asset. Some assets are exempt from Capital Gains Tax. Find out if you are liable for Capital Gains Tax.</li>
	
	<li><a href="/en/money_and_tax/tax/capital_taxes/capital_acquisitions_tax.html">Capital Acquisitions Tax</a><br>If you receive a gift, you may have to pay gift tax on it. If you receive an inheritance following a death, it may be liable to inheritance tax. Both these taxes are types of Capital Acquisitions Tax.</li>
	
	<li><a href="/en/money_and_tax/tax/income_tax/taxation_of_benefits_from_employment.html">Taxation of benefits from employment</a><br>Employees can get certain benefits in addition to their salary or wages. Some of these benefits are taxed. This document provides information on how such benefits are taxed.</li>
	
	</ul>	
